                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d417">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 711.38/107</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Secretary of Embassy <persName type="from">Davis</persName> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-11-03T17:00:00+00:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 3, 1916, 5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your November 2, 7 p.m. The statement made by Ménos is wholly without foundation.
                    I entered into no agreement, either orally or in writing, with respect to the
                    interpretation of Article II, or any other article of Haitian treaty. On the
                    contrary I made a general statement to Minister of Foreign Relations, when the
                    question of interpretation of another article arose, that every article of the
                    treaty must stand on the ordinary meaning of the English text, and with the
                    particular object of guarding against such contingency as has now arisen, I took
                    occasion to make such statement to Minister of Foreign Relations in the presence
                    of Lieutenant E. G. Oberlin.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Davis</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
